n和James Lambourne至少有1個兒子。她去世於1308年之後。"},"zh-hans":{"–after 1308":"–1308年之后","–1308":"–1308年","–1361":"–1361年","after 1308":"1308年之后","1361":"1361年","1308":"1308年","lifeSummary":"Joan和James Lambourne至少有1个儿子。她去世于1308年之后。"},"hr":{"–after 1308":"–nakon 1308.","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"nakon 1308.","1361":"1361","1308":"1308"},"cs":{"–after 1308":"–po 1308","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"po 1308","1361":"1361","1308":"1308"},"da":{"–after 1308":"–efter 1308","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"efter 1308","1361":"1361","1308":"1308"},"nl":{"–after 1308":"–na 1308","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"na 1308","1361":"1361","1308":"1308"},"en":{"–after 1308":"–after 1308","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"after 1308","1361":"1361","1308":"1308","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Joan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan had at least 1 son with James Lambourne. She died after 1308."},"et":{"–after 1308":"–pärast 1308","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"pärast 1308","1361":"1361","1308":"1308"},"fi":{"–after 1308":"–1308 jälkeen","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"1308 jälkeen","1361":"1361","1308":"1308"},"fr":{"–after 1308":"–après 1308","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"après 1308","1361":"1361","1308":"1308","lifeSummary":"Joan a eu au moins 1 fils avec James Lambourne. Elle est décédée après 1308."},"de":{"–after 1308":"–nach 1308","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"nach 1308","1361":"1361","1308":"1308","lifeSummary":"Joan hatte mit James Lambourne mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb nach 1308."},"ht":{"–after 1308":"–after 1308","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"after 1308","1361":"1361","1308":"1308"},"hu":{"–after 1308":"–1308 után","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"1308 után","1361":"1361","1308":"1308"},"id":{"–after 1308":"–setelah 1308","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"setelah 1308","1361":"1361","1308":"1308"},"it":{"–after 1308":"–dopo il 1308","–1308":"–1308","–1361":"–1361","after 1308":"dopo il 1308","1361":"1361","1308":"1308","lifeSummary":"Joan lei avuto almeno 1 figlio con James Lambourne. Morì dopo il 1308."},"ja":{"–after 1308":"–1308年以後","–1308":"–1308年","–1361":"–1361年","after 1308":"1308年以後","1361":"1361年","1308":"1308年","lifeSummary":"JoanはJames Lambourneとの間に少なくとも1人の息子をもうけた。彼女は1308年以後に死去した。"},"ko":{"–after